{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775832379310,"sessionID":"ses_288264b91ffeVOaE91CVgVM8TE","part":{"id":"prt_d77d9c105001ib0MN8pfrWyoiV","messageID":"msg_d77d9b551001eNgbkrx7B8Zp5B","sessionID":"ses_288264b91ffeVOaE91CVgVM8TE","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_d6c40ea56ad54a17a7f32af0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Find AR-011 JWT changes","prompt":"Search the codebase thoroughly for information about AR-011 (Router JWT 认证与签发) in the agentcube project. Look for:\n\n1. Any files in pkg/router related to JWT authentication\n2. Any commit messages, PR descriptions, or documentation mentioning AR-011\n3. Any TODO comments, deferred items, or incomplete implementations\n4. Look at git log for recent commits related to JWT, router, or AR-011\n5. Check for any spec/design documents related to this feature\n\nSearch in the current working directory and any subdirectories. Also check git history.\n\nReturn ALL findings including:\n- What JWT-related files exist in pkg/router\n- What functionality appears to be implemented\n- Any TODO/FIXME/HACK comments indicating deferred work\n- Git commit messages related to this work\n- Any spec or design documents","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288262ee4ffeVMIDuj9HoJv1gb (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive picture of AR-011. Here is the complete report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## AR-011 (Router JWT 认证与签发) -- Complete Search Report\n\n### 1. JWT-RELATED FILES IN `pkg/router`\n\nThe following JWT-related files exist in the `pkg/router` directory:\n\n| File | Absolute Path | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `jwt.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go` | Core JWTManager: key generation, token signing, token validation, K8s Secret persistence |\n| `jwt_test.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | 15 test functions covering JWTManager (275 lines) |\n| `middleware.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go` | Contains `AuthMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager)` -- the JWT auth middleware |\n| `middleware_test.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | 9 test functions covering AuthMiddleware (247 lines) |\n| `config.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/config.go` | Contains `JWTConfig` struct and JWT fields on `Config` |\n| `server.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server.go` | Server initialization with JWTManager, route registration with AuthMiddleware |\n| `proxy.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/proxy.go` | Outbound JWT injection into proxied requests to sandboxes |\n\nOther `pkg/router` files (non-JWT-specific but related):\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/config_test.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server_test.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/errors.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/informer.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/health.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/router.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/loadbalancer.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/backend.go`\n\n---\n\n### 2. FUNCTIONALITY APPEARS TO BE IMPLEMENTED\n\n#### JWTManager (`jwt.go`) -- 182 lines\n- **RSA 2048-bit key generation** on construction (`rsa.GenerateKey`)\n- **`NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig)`** -- accepts optional config; defaults: Expiration=5m, Issuer=\"agentcube-router\", Leeway=1m\n- **`GenerateToken(claims)`** -- RS256-signed tokens with `exp`, `iat`, `iss` base claims + custom claims\n- **`ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString)`** -- validates RS256 signature, checks expiration, issuer; returns human-readable errors (`\"token is expired\"`, `\"invalid signature\"`, `\"invalid issuer\"`, `\"invalid token\"`)\n- **`PublicKey()`** -- accessor for the RSA public key\n- **`TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`** -- persists/loads key pair from K8s Secret `picod-router-identity`; falls back to ephemeral keys outside cluster\n- **`loadPrivateKeyPEM(data)`** -- loads private key from PKCS1 PEM data\n- Uses `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var for namespace (defaults to `\"default\"`)\n\n#### AuthMiddleware (`middleware.go`) -- 102 lines\n- **`AuthMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager)`** -- Gin middleware that:\n  - Extracts `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n  - Returns 401 `{\"error\":\"missing authorization header\",\"code\":\"UNAUTHORIZED\"}` if header missing\n  - Returns 401 `{\"error\":\"invalid authorization format\",\"code\":\"UNAUTHORIZED\"}` if not Bearer format\n  - Calls `jwtManager.ParseAndValidateToken()` and returns 401 `{\"error\":\"token is expired\",\"code\":\"TOKEN_EXPIRED\"}` on expiry\n  - Returns 401 `{\"error\":\"invalid token\",\"code\":\"UNAUTHORIZED\"}` on other validation failures\n  - On success, stores claims in `c.Set(\"claims\", claims)` and calls `c.Next()`\n- Also contains: `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware`, `RequestLoggerMiddleware`, `TraceIDMiddleware`\n\n#### Config (`config.go`) -- 45 lines\n- **`JWTConfig`** struct with `Expiration`, `Issuer`, `Leeway` fields\n- **`Config`** struct extended with `JWTExpiration`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTLeeway` fields\n- **`NewDefaultConfig()`** sets defaults: JWTExpiration=5m, JWTIssuer=\"agentcube-router\", JWTLeeway=1m\n\n#### Server (`server.go`) -- 145 lines\n- **`Server`** struct has `jwtManager *JWTManager` field\n- **`NewServer()`** creates JWTManager from config, calls `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret`\n- **`registerRoutes()`** registers middleware stack on `/v1` group: `Logger -> Recovery -> AuthMiddleware -> ConcurrencyLimit`\n- Health endpoints (`/health/live`, `/health/ready`) registered outside `/v1` group (no auth)\n\n#### Proxy (`proxy.go`) -- 193 lines\n- Outbound JWT injection: when forwarding to `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` kind, generates JWT with `session_id` claim and sets `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n- JWT signing failure returns 500 `{\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\",\"error\":\"failed to sign request\"}`\n- CodeInterpreter kind does NOT get JWT injected\n\n#### Test Coverage\n- `jwt_test.go`: 15 tests covering nil config, custom config, PublicKey, GenerateToken, ParseAndValidateToken (valid, expired, forged, non-RS256, invalid issuer, malformed, empty, leeway, leeway exceeded, concurrent access)\n- `middleware_test.go`: 9 tests covering valid token, missing auth header, invalid format (Basic, empty token), expired token, forged token, custom claims passthrough, malformed token, non-Bearer scheme\n\n---\n\n### 3. TODO/FIXME/HACK COMMENTS\n\n**No TODO, FIXME, HACK, XXX, or DEFERRED comments were found in any `pkg/router/*.go` source files.**\n\nHowever, the `changes/AR-011/tasks.md` file shows all tasks as **unchecked** (`[ ]`), indicating the task tracking document has not been updated to reflect completion status. The 8 task groups (T-001 through T-008) with ~50 sub-tasks are all marked incomplete in the tracking file, even though the code appears to be fully implemented.\n\nThe `changes/AR-011/proposal.md` and `changes/AR-011/design.md` files contain placeholder `<!-- TODO: ... -->` comments in every section, indicating these are template stubs -- the filled-in versions exist at the root level (`/proposal.md` and `/design.md`).\n\n---\n\n### 4. GIT COMMIT MESSAGES\n\nRelevant commits found:\n\n| Commit | Message | Relevance |\n|--------|---------|-----------|\n| `84e4858` | `Regenerate specs from source code (298->1906 lines)` | Likely regenerated `delta-spec.md` from the implemented JWT code |\n| `6c48f1d` | `Complete SDD benchmark: full project generation + validation + reports` | Benchmark completion, may include AR-011 |\n\nNo commits were found with \"JWT\", \"AR-011\", or \"auth\" in the commit message beyond these. The JWT implementation appears to have been created as part of the initial project scaffolding or a squashed commit not visible in the recent 30-commit history.\n\n---\n\n### 5. SPEC AND DESIGN DOCUMENTS\n\n#### Root-Level Documents (Filled In)\n\n| File | Absolute Path | Lines | Status |\n|------|--------------|-------|--------|\n| `proposal.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` | 218 | **Complete** -- Full proposal with purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria |\n| `design.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | 638 | **Complete** -- Detailed design with architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, test strategy, implementation phases, security considerations, and future changes |\n| `delta-spec.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` | 821 | **Complete** -- Actually for AR-009 (Router HTTP Reverse Proxy), but contains JWT-related requirements |\n\n#### `changes/AR-011/` Directory (Templates)\n\n| File | Absolute Path | Lines | Status |\n|------|--------------|-------|--------|\n| `proposal.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-011/proposal.md` | 54 | **Template** -- All sections are `<!-- TODO: ... -->` placeholders |\n| `design.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-011/design.md` | 51 | **Template** -- All sections are `<!-- TODO: ... -->` placeholders |\n| `delta-spec.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md` | 345 | **Complete** -- Detailed delta spec with requirements and scenarios |\n| `tasks.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md` | 152 | **Complete** -- 8 task groups (T-001 to T-008) with ~50 sub-tasks, all unchecked |\n\n#### Other Related Documents\n\n| File | Absolute Path | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `.sdd_prompt.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` | SDD prompt referencing AR-011 with client-go library specs |\n| `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` | TDD manifest defining Test-RT-1 (invalid JWT -> 401) and Test-RT-2 (expired JWT -> Token Expired) |\n\n---\n\n### 6. KNOWN LIMITATIONS (from design.md Section 10)\n\nThe design document explicitly lists these known limitations and future work:\n\n| Future Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------------|-------------|----------|\n| JWT blacklist/revocation list (Redis) | Token revocation capability | P1 |\n| ES256 (ECDSA) signature algorithm support | Alternative signing algorithms | P2 |\n| Role-based access control (RBAC middleware) | Authorization beyond authentication | P2 |\n| Automatic certificate management (cert-manager) | Cert lifecycle automation | P3 |\n| mTLS mutual authentication | Transport-level mutual auth | P3 |\n\n**Current limitations:**\n- Only RS256 algorithm supported (no HS256/ES256)\n- Inbound token validation uses a single public key (router's own keypair), no JWKS multi-key source\n- No token refresh mechanism; clients must handle re-authentication on expiry\n- Key rotation is passive pull mode, no K8s Secret watch for push notifications\n\n---\n\n### 7. IMPLEMENTATION STATUS SUMMARY\n\nThe AR-011 implementation appears **functionally complete** in code:\n\n- `JWTConfig` struct and `Config` extension: **Implemented**\n- `NewJWTManager(config)` with config injection: **Implemented**\n- `JWTManager.PublicKey()`: **Implemented**\n- `JWTManager.ParseAndValidateToken()`: **Implemented**\n- `AuthMiddleware`: **Implemented**\n- `/v1` route group with AuthMiddleware: **Implemented**\n- `/health` endpoints unprotected: **Implemented**\n- Outbound JWT signing in proxy: **Implemented** (preserved from prior work)\n- Unit tests (jwt_test.go, middleware_test.go): **Implemented**\n- K8s Secret key persistence: **Implemented**\n\nWhat is **not done** (based on the design doc's Phase 4 and future changes):\n- `StartKeyRotation()` and `ReloadKeyFromSecret()` methods (key rotation)\n- Environment variable and CLI flag parsing for JWT config\n- `AuthContext` struct with UserID/TenantID/Roles (the design doc proposes this but current implementation stores raw claims directly)\n- `ValidateToken()` method with `AllowedIssuers`/`AllowedAudiences` support (current implementation only checks the single `Issuer`)\n- `GetPublicKeyPEM()` method\n- `proxy_test.go` file (outbound JWT regression tests)\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288262ee4ffeVMIDuj9HoJv1gb","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Find AR-011 JWT changes","time":{"start":1775832256792,"end":1775832379307}}}}
