{"type":"text","timestamp":1775832393359,"sessionID":"ses_288264b91ffeVOaE91CVgVM8TE","part":{"id":"prt_d77dbb9d2001YFBzQyzhLdEzWF","messageID":"msg_d77dbaff80015oHRKLZvDwpPGY","sessionID":"ses_288264b91ffeVOaE91CVgVM8TE","type":"text","text":"## AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发: Archive Summary\n\n### Completed\n\n- **JWTManager core** (`pkg/router/jwt.go`): RSA-2048 key generation, RS256 token signing/validation, K8s Secret persistence (`picod-router-identity`), fallback to ephemeral keys\n- **AuthMiddleware** (`pkg/router/middleware.go`): `Authorization: Bearer` extraction, 401 responses with structured error codes (`UNAUTHORIZED`, `TOKEN_EXPIRED`), claims passthrough via context\n- **Config** (`pkg/router/config.go`): `JWTConfig` struct + `Config` extension with `JWTExpiration`, `JWTIssuer`, `JWTLeeway` and sensible defaults (5m / \"agentcube-router\" / 1m)\n- **Server integration** (`pkg/router/server.go`): JWTManager lifecycle in `NewServer`, middleware stack on `/v1` group (Logger → Recovery → AuthMiddleware → ConcurrencyLimit), health endpoints unauthenticated\n- **Outbound JWT injection** (`pkg/router/proxy.go`): Signs JWT with `session_id` claim for Sandbox/SandboxClaim targets; CodeInterpreter excluded\n- **Test coverage**: 15 tests in `jwt_test.go` (nil config, expired, forged, leeway, concurrent access, etc.) + 9 tests in `middleware_test.go` (missing header, Basic scheme, custom claims, etc.)\n\n### Deferred / Not Implemented\n\n- **Key rotation**: `StartKeyRotation()` and `ReloadKeyFromSecret()` methods — no K8s Secret watch (passive pull only)\n- **Config from env/CLI flags**: JWT settings hardcoded via defaults; no `AGENTCUBE_JWT_*` env parsing or `--jwt-*` flags\n- **`AuthContext` struct**: Design proposes `UserID`/`TenantID`/`Roles` extraction; current impl stores raw claims directly\n- **Multi-issuer/audience validation**: `ValidateToken()` with `AllowedIssuers`/`AllowedAudiences` not implemented; single issuer check only\n- **`GetPublicKeyPEM()`**: accessor not yet added\n- **`proxy_test.go`**: no regression tests for outbound JWT signing\n- **Future algorithms**: ES256/HS256 support, JWKS multi-key source, token refresh, Redis revocation list, RBAC middleware, mTLS — all deferred to P1–P3","time":{"start":1775832393356,"end":1775832393356}}}
